OL,3,CEverything you need to know about
OL,4,CPlymouth's mayor referendum
OL,6,FAccording to a Parliamentary report,
OL,7,Fthe rationale for elected mayors was
OL,8,Fto 'make it clearer to councillors and
OL,9,Fpublic alike where the responsibility
OL,10,Ffor a particular decision lay'.
OL,12,FUnder the leader and cabinet system,
OL,13,Fthe leader must be an elected
OL,14,Fcouncillor. A directly elected mayor
OL,15,Fdoes not need to be a councillor.
OL,17,FWhy is Plymouth having a referendum?
